75
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:02,639
What are you saying?

76
00:05:03,079 --> 00:05:04,199
Am I that kind of person?

77
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:07,730
I told her, but she didn't accept it.

78
00:05:07,730 --> 00:05:08,730
What can I do?

79
00:05:08,879 --> 00:05:10,240
You could have dated anyone.

80
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:12,050
Why do you have to date a female bodyguard?

81
00:05:12,959 --> 00:05:14,879
Do you think you can put up with the beatings?

82
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:19,240
I was young, foolish,

83
00:05:19,879 --> 00:05:21,000
and vain.

84
00:05:21,959 --> 00:05:23,240
Two days ago, Zhu Da Peng said...

85
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,639
we've known each other for three years.

86
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:28,480
Throughout the period,

87
00:05:30,959 --> 00:05:32,319
we spent time together for less than two months.

88
00:05:35,079 --> 00:05:36,160
Tell me.

89
00:05:40,839 --> 00:05:42,800
Is it my fault that he is having an affair?

90
00:05:43,319 --> 00:05:44,399
Even if it were someone else,

91
00:05:44,959 --> 00:05:46,279
that's what would happen too, right?

92
00:05:48,959 --> 00:05:50,040
Not necessarily.

93
00:05:51,199 --> 00:05:52,759
If it were someone else,

94
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:55,800
if he couldn't understand and support your career,

95
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,959
he would have requested a breakup.

96
00:05:56,959 --> 00:05:58,480
It's the least one could do.

97
00:05:59,519 --> 00:06:00,519
He, on the other hand,

98
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:03,839
said that he wants to marry you...

99
00:06:03,839 --> 00:06:05,199
while fooling around with another woman.

100
00:06:05,199 --> 00:06:07,319
What nonsense is this? He's a jerk. A total jerk.

101
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,000
I'm begging you.

102
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:12,680
Don't give him any more excuses. Do you understand?

103
00:06:13,959 --> 00:06:15,279
I trusted him too much.

104
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:17,720
I believed anything he said.

105
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:19,920
He fooled me completely.

106
00:06:24,319 --> 00:06:26,120
Why is love so unreliable?

107
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:31,079
It's not that love is unreliable.

108
00:06:31,639 --> 00:06:34,600
Your relationship with him was never reliable in the first place.

109
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:37,360
You said it yourself. You were together for three years.

110
00:06:37,519 --> 00:06:38,600
Throughout the three years,

111
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,720
you only met up with him when you were on leave.

112
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:43,040
You kept in touch with him through WeChat and video calls.

113
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,800
The pair of you didn't fight or get into conflicts.

114
00:06:45,079 --> 00:06:47,600
The temperature of your relationship is around 30 degrees Celsius.

115
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:48,720
Honey.

116
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:52,279
It's below body temperature.

117
00:06:52,279 --> 00:06:53,879
You would feel cold taking a shower at that temperature.

118
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:58,319
But isn't it better to live a simple life?

119
00:06:58,319 --> 00:06:59,360
What should I do?

120
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:00,399
Should I try to kill myself...

121
00:07:00,399 --> 00:07:01,920
when I haven't seen him for a day?

122
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,040
That's not true.

123
00:07:04,839 --> 00:07:05,920
I'm just curious.

124
00:07:06,839 --> 00:07:08,360
Why is it so hard?

125
00:07:13,199 --> 00:07:14,199
Tell me.

126
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,120
My dad...

127
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,000
has been...

128
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:20,879
struggling all these years.

129
00:07:22,879 --> 00:07:24,639
All his savings are gone.

130
00:07:24,879 --> 00:07:25,920
I know.

131
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:27,680
He's trying to prove my mom wrong.

132
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:28,720
He wants to prove himself.

133
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:30,480
What can I say?

134
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:31,519
I can't say anything.

135
00:07:31,639 --> 00:07:32,639
I'm his daughter.

136
00:07:32,639 --> 00:07:34,680
I have no choice but to help him.

137
00:07:34,839 --> 00:07:35,879
But...

138
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,399
I can't do it anymore.

139
00:07:38,399 --> 00:07:40,199
I've been paying debts for so many years.

140
00:07:40,199 --> 00:07:41,879
I spent all my savings,

141
00:07:41,879 --> 00:07:43,439
but I still haven't cleared all of them.

142
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:47,680
I dated Zhu Da Peng...

143
00:07:48,199 --> 00:07:49,360
for three years.

144
00:07:50,879 --> 00:07:52,040
It's gone just like that.

145
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,079
As for myself,

146
00:07:55,279 --> 00:07:56,720
my stamina is getting worse.

147
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,040
I can't get any big case.

148
00:07:58,399 --> 00:07:59,639
I even got a complaint from a client.

149
00:08:07,839 --> 00:08:09,160
Why is it so hard for me?

150
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,680
I'm so close to breaking down.

151
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:43,879
What are you doing?

152
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:46,240
What are you doing?

153
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:49,240
- I'm going home. - No, please calm down.

154
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:51,720
After I've taken care of what has to be taken care of, we'll...

155
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:52,840
What?

156
00:08:53,799 --> 00:08:55,090
I'm your girlfriend.

157
00:08:55,559 --> 00:08:57,279
Isn't it only right for me to go to your house?

158
00:08:57,559 --> 00:08:58,919
No, I...

159
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:01,799
I don't feel well.

160
00:09:09,759 --> 00:09:11,919
I feel worse.

161
00:09:50,919 --> 00:09:52,279
What a nice house.

162
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:12,279
She got all this for you, right?

163
00:10:14,330 --> 00:10:15,639
I don't think they suit you.

164
00:10:19,330 --> 00:10:21,679
Yes, everything you said is right.

165
00:10:29,330 --> 00:10:31,720
It's huge. What did you buy?

166
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:33,759
Be careful. Don't scratch the door.

167
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:37,720
Move to the left.

168
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:39,960
Slowly.

169
00:10:41,210 --> 00:10:43,159
- My goodness. - What is it, Li Li?

170
00:10:43,159 --> 00:10:45,210
I don't know. Mr. Hou Junior bought it.

171
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:46,559
This way.

172
00:10:47,450 --> 00:10:50,000
Mr. Hou Junior bought it? It's so big.

173
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,210
- Mr. Hou Junior. - It's so big.

174
00:10:51,210 --> 00:10:52,960
- Your parcel is here. - What is it?

175
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:54,279
- He always does this. - That's quick.

176
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:56,240
- Be careful. - Here.

177
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:57,559
Take it apart.

178
00:10:57,799 --> 00:10:58,840
Open it.

179
00:11:02,039 --> 00:11:03,080
It's a chair.

180
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:04,279
Don't scratch it.

181
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:05,480
Slow down.

182
00:11:07,039 --> 00:11:08,720
- Look at this. - I love the color.

183
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,440
What do you think? Touch the leather.

184
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:12,440
It's calfskin leather.

185
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,480
What do you think? Have a seat.

186
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:14,559
I can tell that it's of good quality just by looking.

187
00:11:14,679 --> 00:11:15,679
How is it?

188
00:11:15,919 --> 00:11:17,039
- That feels good. - Doesn't it?

189
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,159
- Give it a try. - Come and see it.

190
00:11:19,159 --> 00:11:20,240
Turn around.

191
00:11:21,399 --> 00:11:22,480
That's my seat.

192
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:25,679
That's an especially good angle.

193
00:11:25,679 --> 00:11:26,960
So it won't hurt your back when you're sitting in the chair.

194
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:28,120
It's comfortable. Do you know that?

195
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:29,919
Sitting in your current chair...

196
00:11:29,919 --> 00:11:31,440
makes your back and legs hurt.

197
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:36,519
Mr. Hou.

198
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,320
Take a seat and give it a try.

199
00:11:40,039 --> 00:11:41,120
What angle?

200
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,519
Where did this chair come from?

201
00:11:43,799 --> 00:11:44,840
I just bought it.

202
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:46,320
You are so rich.

203
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:50,360
This chair doesn't suit you.

204
00:11:52,559 --> 00:11:53,559
Move it.

205
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:55,480
Move it?

206
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:56,919
What do you mean?

207
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:59,120
Are you moving it to your place?

208
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:01,480
Don't do that. I just bought it. Let me try it for two days.

209
00:12:01,639 --> 00:12:03,120
I'll order a new one for you.

210
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:04,679
Thank you, but I don't need it.

211
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:06,879
Office chairs are provided for the employees...

212
00:12:06,879 --> 00:12:08,200
as per the regulations.

213
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:10,759
You can't break the rules for your own comfort.

214
00:12:10,759 --> 00:12:11,799
Do you understand?

215
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:13,879
I mean, my chair...

216
00:12:14,519 --> 00:12:16,519
I don't know how I should put it.

217
00:12:16,519 --> 00:12:18,159
For some reason, after sitting in the chair,

218
00:12:18,159 --> 00:12:20,080
my back as well as my backside hurt.

219
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:22,000
It's really affecting my work.

220
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:23,399
This chair is different.

221
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:25,919
Everyone in the company...

222
00:12:25,919 --> 00:12:28,600
has never lodged a complaint for this very reason.

223
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:30,039
No one is saying anything.

224
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:31,679
You're the only one who feels uncomfortable.

225
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:33,519
Is there a problem here?

226
00:12:33,519 --> 00:12:34,600
Dad, listen.

227
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:36,039
Let me tell you something in a serious manner.

228
00:12:37,039 --> 00:12:38,919
Where is the essence of design?

229
00:12:38,919 --> 00:12:40,799
- Where is it? - It's about the anatomy.

230
00:12:40,799 --> 00:12:42,240
This chair brings so much comfort.

231
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,360
You've been a designer for so long.

232
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:44,519
You should know it very well, right?

233
00:12:44,519 --> 00:12:46,240
I only know the company rules...

234
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:49,360
is more important than your body structure.

235
00:12:49,639 --> 00:12:51,759
Your backside isn't special.

236
00:12:51,759 --> 00:12:53,960
Get this chair out of my sight.

237
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,320
This is not a negotiation.

238
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:57,559
This is an order, okay?

239
00:13:03,759 --> 00:13:04,919
Order?

240
00:13:05,399 --> 00:13:07,159
Does he think he's the president?

241
00:13:07,679 --> 00:13:08,720
I'm not moving it.

242
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:10,080
